subject: Hi Alsu
body:
Hi Alsu,
I’m getting in touch because we provide companies like Lcw with fast funding for working capital and lines of credit, ranging from $150K–800K at just 1% per month.

We offer funding without personal guarantees and don’t run any credit checks. Approval and funding can happen within as little as 24 hours, sometimes even on the same day.

Is this something that benefit you right now, Alsu? Just reply when you have 5–10 min to connect.

Regards,
Oliver Adams
Account Manager
Flex Group

body:

Want to take a few minutes to explore this? I’m open for a quick call today.

Have a great day,
Oliver Adams
Account Manager
Flex Group

body:

The Hartford & Workday Wellness

11:00 AM – 12:00 PM EST 
  
 
  
Register Today 
  
  
  
  
Join us as leaders from The Hartford and Workday unveil how our new tailored solutions and strategic integrations meet the unique needs of today’s workforce. Tune in to: 
  
 
•
Find out how the Workday Wellness experience helps provide personalized wellbeing offerings that can promote healthier and happier workplaces. 
  
 
•
Explore the industry leading benefits for employers who work with The Hartford and Workday for their benefits administration.

subject: Boston Scientific Statement Request: ABOSNA42000148867L
body:
Accounts Receivable,
Boston Scientific is requesting a current Accounts Receivable statement (aging report) from 
LANGUAGE AND CULTURE WORLDWIDE LLC
.  A complete Accounts Receivable statement(s) should include all Open invoices, Open credits (including rebates), Unapplied cash, Prepayments on account, Overpayments, and Duplicate Payments as of the date the report is created (Excel file format preferred).
To avoid additional requests please respond by 8/8/2024.
The purpose of this review is to confirm that all accounts are current and in good standing by ensuring that aged items are processed.  The team responsible for this review consists of both Boston Scientific and APEX Analytix representatives. If additional details/clarifications are required, a member of the team will reach out to you. Your cooperation is appreciated.
Please reply to this email or reference 
ABOSNA42000148867L
 in the subject line when responding to
 
BostonScientific@statements.apexanalytix.com.
If you are not the correct contact for Boston Scientific, please let me know so that I can update our records. 
Thank you for your cooperation.
Andrew Morris

subject: Request for Tax Preparation and Planning Services
body:
Hey there,
I am interested in your tax preparation and planning service. I found your company online, and I wasn't referred by anyone, in case you were wondering.
To save both of our time, I just wanted to ask if you are able to accommodate a new client at this time? If so, please let me know and we can start a conversation.
Thank you for your time.
Sincerely,
Jeff Carlson.

subject: [UPCOMING WEBINAR] ERP Name + Stampli AP automation
body:
Learn how Stampli can help you can automate your accounts payable processes without reworking your QuickBooks Desktop ERP.
 
 
 
Invitation
Stampli Connects
 
 
Automate AP without reworking your QuickBooks Desktop ERP
 
Are you tired of struggling with the inefficiencies of manual accounts payable processes? 
Perhaps you have even considered automating AP, but were deterred by the risk of disrupting your ERP or the expense of hiring deployment consultants. 
If this sounds familiar, then we invite you to join one of our weekly webinars focused on automating AP without disturbing your QuickBooks Desktop ERP.
During 
this webinar
, you will discover how Stampli can help you:
Reduce disruption
: No need to rework your QBD ERP or change your AP processes.
Gain more control
: One place for all your communication, documentation, and workflows.
Benefit from advanced AI
: Billy the Bot assists you across the entire invoice process — and he’s always learning.
Get the fastest time-to-value
: Stampli deploys in days, not months, with minimal user training, and without expensive consultants.
Unlock more than just AP
: Stampli offers integrated payments, credit cards, vendor management, AP data insights, and more.
Can't make it to the live session? No worries. You can still register to receive the on-demand recording after.
 
 
Register Now

experts

subject: eSupplier Upgrade
body:
You don't often get email from minneapolis@public.govdelivery.com. 
Learn why this is important
Hello, the City of Minneapolis will be upgrading our finance system, which includes eSupplier, over this weekend.  eSupplier will be down from 4:00 PM Friday, May 31, through the weekend and back up on  Monday morning.  Please make sure that if you have a bid to place before the weekend, that you do so right away.  There should not be any contract opportunities that will be closing around the times that the system will be down.
eSupplier will have a new, more modern look to it.  All of the same information will be there, but the look will be different.
We have also created videos and new instructions for how to sign in, navigate within, reset password, setup users within your company, and more.  The videos and instructions will be posted to 
https://www.minneapolismn.gov/business-services/doing-business-with-the-city/esupplier-instructions/guides-forms/
Please visit this page starting Monday, June 3, to view the videos and revised instructions.
If you have any questions regarding the transition to the new look of eSupplier, please feel free to contact 
eProcurement@minneapolismn.gov
Thanks
City Finance Staff
 
Finance and Property Services - Procurement
505 Fourth Avenue South, Room 310, Minneapolis, MN 55415
www.minneapolismn.gov/finance/procurement
For reasonable accommodations or alternative formats please contact 311 at 612-673-3000.
People who are deaf or hard of hearing can use a relay service to call 311 at 612-673-3000. 
TTY users call 612-263-6850.

subject: Use GenAI to Access Your CAT-Tool and TMS Shortcuts, and More; Join My Zoom Call Tomorrow
body:

Email: sbammel@koreanconsulting.com

StevenBammel.com
Resume
 - 
"Consistently Good Work" Pledge
Hi,
Can you remember all the shortcuts to use on your computer, from your TMS to your other language and non-language programs? Of course not! Who can remember all of those?
Here’s an easy hack… Paste all of your keyboard shortcut cheat sheets into a single text file with the following prompt:
[unformatted keyboard shortcut cheat sheet content]
The above is unformatted content from the keyboard shortcut cheat sheets for all of my Windows programs. I need you to analyze and search the keyboard shortcut cheat sheets above and answer my questions.
IMPORTANT: When answering a question, if the answer is not in the cheat sheet, you can still try to answer, but make sure you tell me in your answer that it is not in the cheat sheet.
Tell me the keyboard shortcuts for the following action:
Then keep this file handy. The next time you want to jog your memory, paste the entire text file into ChatGPT or Copilot and write out what you’re looking for (ex.: “Copy source to target in memoQ”).
Bingo! You’ll get your answer.
But this would be a lot easier in CotranslatorAI, and it is just one of several use cases I’ll be demonstrating tomorrow in our 45-minute Zoom call. 
In addition to new use cases, I will also showcase the new CotranslatorAI features, editions, and training, and will offer a 50% discount to boot.

Steven

subject: Designing a positive future -  Earth Day and every day
body:
You don't often get email from no-reply@ecom1.logitech.com. 
Learn why this is important
It's time to work together to create a better world.
 ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌   ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌   ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌   ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌   ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌   ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌   ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌   ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌   ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌   ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌   ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌   ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌   ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌   ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌   ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌   ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌   ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌   ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌  ͏ ‌   
 
 
 
 
 
DESIGNING A POSITIVE FUTURE
 
 
 
 
 
 
Our goal? To design for sustainability. 
 
That means we consider environmental and social impacts as part of every design decision, from the moment raw materials are sourced to the product’s end of life. We are looking for hidden impacts to reduce a product’s carbon footprint in any way possible.
 
 
FIND OUT HOW
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
Choose color. Choose design.
 
We have an established recycled plastic program which promotes the use of post-consumer recycled (PCR) plastic as an alternative to virgin plastic in our devices. We use PCR plastic to give a second life to end-of-life plastic and help reduce our carbon footprint. We are applying PCR at scale across the company, targeting our largest product portfolios for the most impactful carbon reduction.
 
LEARN MORE
 
EXPLORE PRODUCTS
 
 
 
 
From recycled plastics to new possibilities
 
 
 
MX Keys Mini in Black plastic parts are 30% certified post-consumer recycled plastic. 
 
 
 
MX KEYS MINI
 
MX Anywhere 3s in Pale Gray plastic parts are 61% certified post-consumer recycled plastic.
 
 
 
MX ANYWHERE 3S
 
Zone Vibe 100 parts are 25% certified post-consumer recycled plastic.
 
 
 
ZONE VIBE 100
 
 
 
 
The recycled plastic content has been verified by a third-party source. Certification includes post-consumer recycled plastic in all color variants.
 
 
 
SEE ALL PRODUCTS
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
Take action, find your local recycling center
 
Logitech devices have parts that can be recycled and used to make new products. Recycle your old devices to give materials, parts and components a second life.
 
RECYCLE NOW
 
 
 
 
Simple everyday decisions can lead to a better future. Society is facing big challenges and we can see how the logic of the past has contributed to those challenges. Together we can take action for a sustainable, equitable, and climate-positive world. 
Thank you for making a difference and participating in the Logitech journey.

MEET. STREAM. MASTER.
 
 
MX BRIO 4K Ultra HD Collaboration and Streaming Webcam
 
 
 
LEARN MORE
 
BUY NOW
 
 
 
OUR MOST ADVANCED WEBCAM YET
 
 
 
UP TO 2X BETTER PERFORMANCE THAN BRIO 4K (1)
Make sure that you are seen, even in difficult lighting conditions, such as in low light or when you are backlit. The webcam’s AI face-based image enhancements, auto-exposure, auto white balance ensure that you keep looking your best.
 
 
 
 
 
 
PUT YOUR WORK IN SHOW MODE
Tilt down your webcam and share your notes and sketches on your desk with Show Mode, all while on a call, for better collaboration.
 
 
 
SHOP MX BRIO
 
 
 
 
CUSTOMIZE WITH ADVANCED CONTROLS
 
 
Customize your video in Logi Options+ with Fine Controls3. Adjust lighting, white balance, ISO, Shutter Speed, tint, vibrance, and more or just let Auto mode take care of it.
 
 
 
 
 
 
SHOP MX BRIO
 
 
 
HIGH PERFORMANCE. ENGINEERED RESPONSIBLY
 
 
 
MADE WITH RECYCLED PLASTICS
The plastic parts in MX Brio include a minimum of 82% for Graphite, and 75% for Pale Gray certified post-consumer recycled plastic. Excludes packaging.
 
LOW-CARBON ALUMINUM
The aluminum in the MX Brio camera housing is made with renewable energy rather than fossil fuels.
 
RESPONSIBLE PACKAGING
The paper packaging of MX Brio comes from FSC™-certified forests and other controlled sources.
 
CERTIFIED CARBON NEUTRAL
This means the carbon impact of the product and packaging has been reduced to zero due to Logitech’s investment in carbon-offsetting and removal projects.

This is a reminder message requesting that you complete your Supplier Registration profile in order to be set up as a registered supplier in the WPP Supplier database. If you recently received an invitation to register, it was at the request of one of the agencies  FinancePlus services. The agency intends to engage with your company as a Supplier.
Please complete your registration and submit so we can activate your company on our vendor master file.
Updating your profile connects you with our supplier self-service portal. 
This portal allows you to update your supplier information (Legal name, Address, Contact Information, Banking, etc) as well as track the progress of your outstanding invoices. 
Updates made to your supplier record are reviewed and maintained in our vendor master file keeping your information current and minimizing delays in processing your invoices.
While you may not have current invoices pending, you are still active in our system and therefore can update your record. This insures your information is accurate and current should you need to submit future invoices.
How to update your profile?
 
Visit: 
https://wpp.apexanalytix.com/
 to login with the user name and password sent on the original invitation.
 
If you have lost or deleted the original invitation email,  please  reply using this email  to FPUS.vendorportal@financeplususa.com and request the invitation be resent

nd

.

the registration
.

documents are required to be uploaded at the end of the registration

W9: 
US based Supplier ( upload, or electronic sign W9 within Portal)

US/CAD

o

subject: Heads-up: Scoro Wrapped will be released on January 31.
body:
You don't often get email from hello@scoro.com. 
Learn why this is important
We’re contacting you to let you know that we’ll be releasing Scoro Wrapped on January 31st to all your site users. 
 
 
Dear Scoro site admin,
We’re contacting you to let you know that we’ll be releasing 
Scoro Wrapped on January 31st
 to all your site users. 
What is Scoro Wrapped?
Scoro Wrapped is Scoro’s version of a year-in-review based on individual statistics. Each user will see a fun summary of their 2023 based on data in Scoro, such as their most productive day, most productive month, time spent in meetings, etc. By default, everyone will have the option to share these insights on LinkedIn to showcase their achievements.
 
Here’s a little sneak peek of what to expect:
 
What action is required from you?
No action is required if you are happy to let your team share such insights on LinkedIn.
 
However, we understand the importance of privacy and control. Therefore, we’re also giving you the option to disable direct sharing to LinkedIn before Scoro Wrapped becomes available for your site users.
 
To disable the sharing, go to 
Settings > Administration > Security settings
 and untick the respective setting. This way, the LinkedIn share button will be greyed out on the Scoro Wrapped cards.
 
Scoro Wrapped will be available for all users until February 8th. You can disable or enable the sharing option anytime between January 29th and February 8th.
 
Team Scoro
P.S. You’re receiving this email because you are listed as a billing or primary point of contact for an existing Scoro account.
 
 
 
 
© 2023 Scoro Software. | 
www.scoro.com
If you need assistance or have any questions, please contact our 
Customer Support
.
You are receiving this email because you have a Scoro account. For more information about how we process data, please see our 
Privacy Policy
.
Scoro Software, 81 Rivington Street, London, England EC2A 3AY, United Kingdom

Woweeee! Welcome to 2024! With all the “In and Out” lists floating around the internet this month, we thought, hey, we have opinions! Let’s whip up our own! So, without further ado, here is our completely biased, absolutely not fact-checked 
Postable Picks: 2024 Ins-and-Outs List
.  
 
XOXO (wait, saying XOXO is probably definitely out!?) 
The Postable Fam 
Behold the list!
 
In: Homemade Cocktails
Save your cash without sacrificing your taste buds this year and whip up your own deeeeelicious DIY drinks. This 
Snow Day Sour
 is calling our names. 
 
Out: Cold Hands
Cold feet remain in, but cold hands? Irrevocably out! Gloves and mittens are a given for chilly temps outdoors, but we’re also maybe actually about to purchase these 
keyboard hand warmers
? 
 
In: Glowing Plants
Why use a night light when you could enjoy a little bedtime reading under the soft glow of… a 
bioluminescent petunia plant
!? You’re welcome. 
 
Out: Paper Straws
We aren’t saying we don’t want eco-friendly straw options! But those paper straws? They just get sooo mushy. We’re planning to bring these 
gorgeous stainless steel straws
 (there’s even a boba size!) with us everywhere this year. 
 
In: Leaving the Christmas Lights Up ‘Til January
Do it! You worked so hard to put those lights up in the first place. Anddd Taylor Swift 
already confirmed you could
! 
Out: Chaotic Closets
Free yourself from the chaotic closet tyranny! Our very own "Modern Martha," Elise, is back with essential tips to 
organize your closet
. No crazy folding strategy or nostalgic tears required! 
 
In: Sending real cards
C’monnnn, sending birthday 
texts 
is soooo 2019. Real cards are where it's at, baby! Want to really go the extra mile? 
Join Postable Plus
, our delightful new subscription service.  
 
…well, how’d we do?

subject: AI Won't Work for You in Translation If It Doesn't Inspire You
body:
Get Inspired by My GenAI for LSPs Workshop
 
View this email in your browser
Steven S. Bammel, PhD
Korean-to-English Translator
Email: sbammel@koreanconsulting.com
Website: 
StevenBammel.com
Resume
 - 
"Consistently Good Work" Pledge
Hi,
I am inspired by Generative AI (GenAI). 
I’m also worried about the future. At this point, nobody knows what the long-term impact of AI will be.
But one thing I do know: The AI is just too powerful and useful to ignore. And the opportunities—at least in the short-term—are significant. For these reasons, I have been obsessed with GenAI since late 2022. 
For the last couple months, I have been approaching my LSP clients to share what I’ve learned. My goal is to inspire you to get started with GenAI in translation. Having given a number of these webinars already, my content has now become a two-hour workshop that covers the following:
GenAI has superpowers.
GenAI will make you more productive.
Here’s how AI-savvy linguists are using GenAI right now.
As a project manager, you can use GenAI in your daily work, too.
Generative AI Iterative Translation (GAIT) is a next-generation workflow.
You can support your linguists during the GenAI transition.
Consider these four ideas to keep moving forward.
In this information-packed, hands-on workshop, I share 12 sophisticated prompts ready for you to apply in your work. I also show you how to do it using CotranslatorAI, the tool that Stanislav Okhvat and I are developing. I even provide you with a temporary API key that gives you access to OpenAI’s most powerful GenAI model so you can see and use the AI’s full power.
I start right from the basics, so you do not need to know about GenAI already. But I also introduce brand-new insights. So whether you’ve barely even checked out ChatGPT or have been exploring GenAI solutions for awhile, I guarantee you will learn a lot.
This is a FREE Zoom workshop to inspire your team of project managers and others in your company involved in the translation process.
If you’d like to find out more, email me by replying to this email (or just contact me at sbammel@koreanconsulting.com). 
I’d love to discuss this with you!
Steven
BTW, I just presented an ATA-hosted presentation last week. To watch the recording (including the additional 30-minutes of content I included afterward), check out this link: 
The AI Transformation: Practical Use of CotranslatorAI
What you can expect when you work with me:
Accurate, well-written, and well-formatted translations of your documents
On-time delivery every time, sometimes with overnight turnaround
Prompt and thorough communication before, during, and after your project
Single source for both English-to-Korean and Korean-to-English translation
I personally translate every Korean-to-English translation project myself.
My team and I work together on a best-practice, six-eye translation-edit-QA process for English-to-Korean translation jobs.
Consistently high quality from project to project by leveraging the latest technology and best-practice workflows
Transparent pricing structure that includes CAT and volume discounts
Workflow verifiability, US-based business registration, professional liability insurance, and my “Consistently Good Work” Pledge
Confidential handling of and respect for your intellectual property, including workflow options with additional security
Services I provide:
Korean>English translation
English>Korean translation
English>Korean trans-edit-QA
Korean>English revision
The main fields I work in:
Business management
Finance & accounting
Corporate/business legal
Intellectual property
Public sector
Medical & pharmaceutical

subject: Request for proposal of Individual Intercultural communication coaching sessions with Native English coach -J&J Learning and Development Programme - Language and culture worldwide
body:
Dear Alsu Schondelmayer,
 
I hope you are well.
 
I have been contacted by the business for the 
delivery of Individual Intercultural communication coaching sessions with Native English coach.
 
Please find the below information relating to the training.
 
Participant’s background
: 
she is senior director of the Learning & Development department, promoted last year into this role, a global role that requires her to interact mainly with the US and leadership level as well as employee level. The focus of the coaching is about better understand the cultural differences when presenting information but at the same time, preparing the right information for the audience in the meeting as different audiences require different approaches. Claudine sometimes tends to go too much in detail when presenting to management, losing management’s attention for that reason, or she is not able to clearly articulate the key messages she wants to get across, message gets lost in the details.
 
F2F/Online
: Participant based in France, so virtual sessions are fine.
 
Number of requested sessions
:  she would suggest starting with 5 sessions with the option to extend to 10 if needed.
 
Timing:

subject: [Expensify] New for 2024: Budgets to keep your expenses in check
body:
You don't often get email from davidb@expensify.com. 
Learn why this is important
It's the season for reflecting on how last year went, and what can be done to make this year better.  One common refrain is asking "how did I end up spending so much on that?"  The answer is generally pretty simple: one small purchase at a time, with a steady trickle that added up faster than expected.  With that in mind, 
we're very happy to announce "tag and category budgets"
 – the easiest way to catch these financial leaks before they flood your basement.   
 
The feature works exactly as its name implies:
Edit an 
expense category or tag
 (like, "Travel expenses" or "Project X"). 
Pick a 
budget period
 (such as "monthly", or "yearly"). 
Assign a 
total workspace budget
, summed across all workspace members (in case you have multiple, though this works great for sole-proprietors with no employees as well). 
Assign a 
per-member budget
, to regulate each individual member's spend. 
Hit Save, and we'll let you know:
Whenever anyone spends over 50% (or whatever threshold you pick) of the budget for the first time this period. 
And again once the budget has been 100% used.
The notification is delivered via email, as well as in New Expensify to your workspace's #admins room, with a link taking you straight to the spend so you can update your forecast.  It's an easy solution to a hard problem, and you can set it up three different ways:
Ask your account manager to set up a call to walk you through it.
Read more about 
tag and category budgets online
. 
Or just hit 
edit
 on your favorite tag or category and set it up. 
As the old saying goes: 
The best time to 
plant a tree
 
create a budget was a long time ago.  The next best time is right now.  
 
Give budgets a shot and make 2024 your best year yet!
-david
Founder and CEO of Expensify
Questions?  Ask me on 
Twitter
 X! 
@dbarrett
 
PS: 
New Expensify
 is starting to get really good.  It's already great at settling friend-to-friend debts, splitting bills between groups of friends, and chatting in groups across platforms (Android, iOS, web, with both your email and SMS contacts).  But coming real soon here is full blown multi-organization enterprise chat and task management – not to mention a truly realtime take on financial collaboration inside and between companies.  2024 is going to be a big year for the Expensify community.  Get ready! 
Sent by: Expensify, Inc. - 548 Market St #61434 - San Francisco, CA 94103
